<doc id="1157906" wikidata="Q2753058" url="?curid=1157906" title="Maelgwn">
<text>Maelgwn is a Middle Welsh personal name meaning &#x27;Princely Hound&#x27;, stemming from Common Brittonic *&quot;Maglo-kunos&quot;, attested in Latin as &quot;Maglocunus&quot;. A number of Welsh kings and princes have borne the name:

* Maelgwn Gwynedd (died 547), king of Gwynedd
*Maelgwn ab Owain Gwynedd (died c. 1173), son of Owain Gwynedd and ruler of Anglesey
* Maelgwn ap Rhys (c. 1170 - 1230), son of Rhys ap Gruffydd and ruler of part of Deheubarth</text><links>
