<doc id="1157943" wikidata="Q4903455" url="?curid=1157943" title="Bibliography of the Sierra Nevada">
<text>The following is a bibliography of the Sierra Nevada of California, United States, including books on recreation, natural history, and human history.
==Recreation==

===General travel===
*&quot;Yosemite &amp; The Southern Sierra Nevada: A Complete Guide, Including Sequoia &amp; Kings Canyon, Death Valley &amp; Mammoth Lakes (Great Destinations)&quot; (2008), by David T. Page, .
*&quot;Sierra Nevada byways : backcountry drives for the whole family&quot; (2008), by Tony Huegel, , Wilderness Press.

===Hiking and climbing===

*&quot;Discovering the John Muir Trail: An Inspirational Guide to America&#x27;s Most Beautiful Hike&quot; (2018) by Damon Corso, .
*&quot;Moon Yosemite, Sequoia &amp; Kings Canyon Hiking, Camping, Waterfalls &amp; Big Trees&quot; (2015) by Ann Marie Brown, .
*&quot;Climbing Mt. Whitney,&quot; (2007) by Peter Croft and Wynne Benti, 3rd edition, 42nd printing, , Spotted Dog Press, Bishop, CA.
*&quot;John Muir Trail: The Essential Guide to Hiking America&#x27;s Most Famous Trail&quot; (2007), 4th edition, by Elizabeth Wenk with Kathy Morey, .
*&quot;Sierra South: Backcountry Trips in California&#x27;s Sierra Nevada&quot; (2006) by Kathy Morey and Mike White, with Stacy Corless, Analise Elliot, Chris Tirrell, and Thomas Winnett, Wilderness Press, .
*&quot;Sierra North: Backcountry Trips in California&#x27;s Sierra Nevada&quot; (2005) by Kathy Morey and Mike White, with Stacy Corless and Thomas Winnett, Wilderness Press, 9th edition, .
*&quot;Feather River Country Adventure Trails...&quot; (2004), by Tom Demund, .
*&quot;Close Ups of the High Sierra,&quot; (2004) by Norman Clyde, 2nd edition, 3rd printing, , Spotted Dog Press, Bishop CA.
*&quot; Woman on the Rocks: The Mountaineering Letters of Ruth Dyar Mendenhall&quot; (2004), 1st edition, , Spotted Dog Press, Bishop, CA.
*&quot;100 Hikes in Yosemite,&quot; (2003) by Marc J. Soares, Mountaineers Books, .
*&quot;Starr&#x27;s Guide to the John Muir Trail and the High Sierra Region&quot; (2002) 12th rev. ed., by Walter A. Starr, Jr. .
*&quot;The Good, the Great, and the Awesome: The Top 40 High Sierra Rock Climbs&quot; (2002), by Peter Croft, .
*&quot;Hiking in the Sierra Nevada&quot;, (2002) by John Mock and Kimberley O&#x27;Neil, , A Lonely Planet guidebook.
*&quot;Yuba trails 2: A selection of historic hiking trails in the Yuba River and neighboring watersheds&quot; (2001), by Hank Meals, ASIN B0006RSO5U.
*&quot;The High Sierra: Peaks, Passes, and Trails&quot; (1999), by R. J. Secor, .
*&quot;The Tahoe Sierra: A Natural History Guide to 112 Hikes in the Northern Sierra&quot; (1998), by Jeffrey Schaffer, Wilderness Press, .
*&quot;The Secret Sierra: The Alpine World Above the Trees&quot; (1998), by David Gilligan, 1st edition, , Spotted Dog Press, Bishop CA.
*&quot;Climbing California&#x27;s Fourteeners: The Route Guide to the Fifteen Highest Peaks&quot; (1998) by Stephen Porcella and Cameron Burns, .
*&quot;Sierra High Route: Traversing Timberline Country&quot; (1997), by Steve Roper, .
*&quot;Sierra Classics : 100 Best Climbs in the High Sierra&quot; (1993), by John Moynier and Claude Fiddler, .
*&quot;The Tahoe-Yosemite Trail: A Comprehensive Guide...&quot; (1987), by Thomas Winnett, Wilderness Press, .
*&quot;Yosemite Climbs&quot; (1987), by George Meyers and Don Reid, .
*&quot;The Vertical World of Yosemite&quot; (1973), by Royal Robbins, .

===Skiing===

*&quot;Backcountry Skiing California&#x27;s High Sierra&quot; (1999), by John Moynier, .
*&quot;Ski Tours in the Sierra Nevada: East of the Sierra&quot; (1986), by Marcus Libkind, .
*&quot;Ski Tours in the Sierra Nevada: Lake Tahoe&quot; (1985), by Marcus Libkind, .
