<text>The Mayer f-function is an auxiliary function that often appears in the series expansion of thermodynamic quantities related to classical many-particle systems. It is named after chemist and physicist Joseph Edward Mayer.

==Definition==
Consider a system of classical particles interacting through a pair-wise potential
