where the bold labels formula_2 and formula_3 denote the continuous degrees of freedom associated with the particles, e.g., 
:formula_4
for spherically symmetric particles and
:formula_5
for rigid non-spherical particles where formula_6 denotes position and formula_7 the orientation parametrized e.g. by Euler angles. The Mayer f-function is then defined as
:formula_8
where formula_9 the inverse absolute temperature in units of energy−1 .

